hopobject.body: Could I have an application form? prescription drugs public policy The Federal Reserve said it will "await more evidence" on the state of the economic recovery before it begins scaling back its $85-billion-per-month bond-buying program. Wall Street analysts broadly expected the central bank to begin tapering at this meeting. A set of projections provided along with the statement said most members of the Fed's policy-setting board expect to begin raising short-term interest rates in 2015.
